gloss:IsometricEmbedding a mathkg:GlossRecord ;
    rdfs:label "Isometric embedding gloss record" ;
    mathkg:canonicalGloss "Isometric embedding: Let $(M,g)$ and $(N,h)$ be Riemannian manifolds. An isometric embedding is a smooth embedding $f : M \\\\to N$ which preserves the metric in the sense that $g$ is equal to the pullback of $h$ by $f$, i.e. $g = f*h$." ;
    mathkg:conciseForm "Isometric embedding: Let $(M,g)$ and $(N,h)$ be Riemannian manifolds. An isometric embedding is a smooth embedding $f : M \\\\to N$ which preserves the metric in the sense that $g$ is equal to the pullback of $h$ by $f$, i.e. $g = f*h$." ;
    mathkg:documentRoleForm "In a mathematical document, isometric embedding usually signals a scalar concept with provenance from OntoMathPRO." ;
    mathkg:domainTag "general-mathematics" ;
    mathkg:expertForm "Isometric embedding denotes let $(M,g)$ and $(N,h)$ be Riemannian manifolds. An isometric embedding is a smooth embedding $f : M \\\\to N$ which preserves the metric in the sense that $g$ is equal to the pullback of $h$ by $f$, i.e. $g = f*h$." ;
    mathkg:glossForConcept mathkg:Isometricembedding ;
    mathkg:pedagogicalForm "Think of isometric embedding as let $(M,g)$ and $(N,h)$ be Riemannian manifolds. An isometric embedding is a smooth embedding $f : M \\\\to N$ which preserves the metric in the sense that $g$ is equal to the pullback of $h$ by $f$, i.e. $g = f*h$." ;
    mathkg:sourceProvenance "OntoMathPRO" ;
    mathkg:sourceProvenanceNote "Selected from OntoMathPRO English-labeled class inventory to complete the 500 target concept layer." ;
    dcterms:source <http://cll.niimm.ksu.ru/ontologies/mathematics#E1350> ;
    skos:prefLabel "Isometric embedding" .

